  in retrospective , david weigel of bloomberg businessweek called the contempt of congress vote " both popular and stunningly ineffective , enraging holder and turning him into a more outspoken and implacable foe of republican policies on voting rights and policing . "   in august 2014 , federal judge amy berman jackson ordered the justice department to provide congress with some of the previously withheld documents that had led congress to hold holder in contempt .

